1
00:00:01,090 --> 00:00:04,590
ALL CITIZENS SHALL BE ENTITLED
TO A LIFE WORTHY OF HUMAN BEINGS

2
00:00:04,680 --> 00:00:07,430
THE STATE SHALL ENDEAVOR
TO PREVENT DISASTERS

3
00:00:07,510 --> 00:00:10,430
AND TO PROTECT CITIZENS
FROM HARM THEREFROM

4
00:00:10,520 --> 00:00:12,680
ARTICLE 34 OF THE CONSTITUTION
OF THE REPUBLIC OF KOREA

5
00:00:18,360 --> 00:00:19,940
Jun-ho, hey!

6
00:00:21,230 --> 00:00:23,900
Don't worry. We're the only ones
in the world looking for this guy.

7
00:00:23,990 --> 00:00:25,070
Come on, drink up, huh?

8
00:00:25,160 --> 00:00:26,450
D.P.!

9
00:00:26,530 --> 00:00:27,530
That's right, let loose.

10
00:00:28,450 --> 00:00:31,910
Welcome to the Dirty Players Club!

11
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:34,330
Only then do we catch the bastard.

12
00:00:41,460 --> 00:00:42,800
Wake up, Jun-ho.

13
00:00:44,090 --> 00:00:45,970
Why do you look so hideous?

14
00:00:49,640 --> 00:00:52,310
So how have you been?

15
00:00:55,140 --> 00:00:58,810
Remember how I got kicked out of the unit
right after you beat the hell out of me?

16
00:00:58,900 --> 00:00:59,980
After that…

17
00:01:02,110 --> 00:01:04,820
because of these rumors
of how I was a deadbeat loser,

18
00:01:05,570 --> 00:01:07,570
my father lost his reelection.

19
00:01:08,160 --> 00:01:09,910
And due to the fact
that he took out loans,

20
00:01:09,990 --> 00:01:11,990
our family's got fucking wrecked now.

21
00:01:13,580 --> 00:01:17,170
I wanted to study abroad
after I got discharged.

22
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:21,460
I can't study shit, man.

23
00:01:24,260 --> 00:01:27,430
I became a non-com
and extended my service to survive.

24
00:01:30,180 --> 00:01:32,930
Are you saving to study abroad?

25
00:01:34,220 --> 00:01:37,140
I spent the whole last year
building my body. Why?

26
00:01:38,230 --> 00:01:40,360
So the next time I saw you, I'd kill you.

27
00:01:41,440 --> 00:01:42,610
It's amusing, isn't it?

28
00:01:46,240 --> 00:01:48,240
You haven't changed at all.

29
00:01:50,530 --> 00:01:52,910
Can you bastards shut
your damn mouths?

30
00:01:58,750 --> 00:02:02,340
Hot-headed kids like you can't separate
your personal life from the work, can you?

31
00:02:02,920 --> 00:02:05,420
You should've checked the contents
before you destroyed it,

32
00:02:05,510 --> 00:02:06,630
you goddamn idiot.

33
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:10,720
I'm sorry, sir.

34
00:02:14,350 --> 00:02:16,560
All right, it's done. Fuck!

35
00:02:28,610 --> 00:02:29,700
What is this?

36
00:02:30,570 --> 00:02:33,530
DON'T JUST THROW AWAY YOUR COMPUTER
CALL ME FOR REPAIRS AND BACKUP!

37
00:02:33,620 --> 00:02:35,950
So you're saying
there's no way to copy this?

38
00:02:36,040 --> 00:02:38,120
But there has to be something you can do.

39
00:02:42,380 --> 00:02:44,540
I don't usually do stuff like this, okay?

40
00:02:50,260 --> 00:02:52,800
If we switch out the chip
with this one here,

41
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:55,560
then that chip would be empty.

42
00:02:57,220 --> 00:02:58,350
Okay?

43
00:02:59,100 --> 00:03:00,690
What the fuck?

44
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:06,440
Is the original at that shop?

45
00:03:12,570 --> 00:03:14,320
Do I look like a moron?

46
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:35,030
12. THE DAY

47
00:04:37,990 --> 00:04:38,910
Sir!

48
00:04:38,990 --> 00:04:43,660
A MILITARY CULTURE CREATED TOGETHER

49
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:47,630
You crazy bastards.

50
00:04:48,130 --> 00:04:50,090
You assholes have lost your damn minds.

51
00:04:50,670 --> 00:04:53,170
Showing insubordination
to a superior officer.

52
00:04:53,260 --> 00:04:54,880
This is an unbelievable disgrace!

53
00:04:55,470 --> 00:04:58,430
You disobeyed your mission.
You helped him get away.

54
00:04:58,930 --> 00:05:02,180
He's not just a deserter,
he stole top-secret intel.

55
00:05:02,270 --> 00:05:04,930
It's a matter of national security,
do you understand?

56
00:05:05,020 --> 00:05:06,270
Apologies, sir.

57
00:05:09,190 --> 00:05:10,480
Han Ho-yeol.

58
00:05:11,230 --> 00:05:14,690
Fuck, your entire military service
amounted to a pile of shit. Jesus!

59
00:05:14,780 --> 00:05:16,570
Even your final days.

60
00:05:16,650 --> 00:05:17,780
Oh, God.

61
00:05:18,990 --> 00:05:20,030
And Beom-gu,

62
00:05:21,080 --> 00:05:24,950
You let yourself be swayed by these
lower-rank bastards, for fuck's sake?

63
00:05:25,750 --> 00:05:27,370
Okay, we're all finished here.

64
00:05:28,960 --> 00:05:30,540
Right. Great work.

65
00:05:36,220 --> 00:05:37,550
You're on standby.

66
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:40,720
Don't even think about
stepping off this base.

67
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:51,810
This drives me crazy.

68
00:05:57,650 --> 00:06:00,820
The way things are,
won't Jun-ho be court-martialed?

69
00:06:00,910 --> 00:06:02,200
It looks like it.

70
00:06:02,910 --> 00:06:05,950
He could go to military prison if
they charge him with aggravated assault.

71
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:09,290
What the hell is on that USB that
could cause him to take things this far?

72
00:06:09,370 --> 00:06:11,460
-Sergeant Park--
-Don't ask what I plan on doing,

73
00:06:11,540 --> 00:06:12,750
because I don't know yet.

74
00:06:13,420 --> 00:06:14,630
No, that's not it.

75
00:06:21,090 --> 00:06:23,390
My delayed discharge,
I think I'm ready now.

76
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:28,350
What are you doing now?

77
00:06:28,430 --> 00:06:30,060
He said my service amounted to shit

78
00:06:30,140 --> 00:06:32,730
so I should speak with him,
in private, before I go.

79
00:06:34,190 --> 00:06:35,110
Salute.

80
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:37,320
Bye-bye.

81
00:06:37,900 --> 00:06:39,400
Hey, Han Ho-yeol! Wait!

82
00:06:39,490 --> 00:06:40,530
I'm free!

83
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:53,290
-Sir, there's a phone call for you.
-What is it?

84
00:06:53,380 --> 00:06:54,380
They said it's urgent.

85
00:06:54,460 --> 00:06:56,090
Moron, I asked you what it is?

86
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:01,840
Hello?

87
00:07:04,640 --> 00:07:05,810
Who are you?

88
00:07:07,930 --> 00:07:10,180
Wow.

89
00:07:10,980 --> 00:07:13,150
Being discharged is so nice.

90
00:07:16,320 --> 00:07:17,320
Hello.

91
00:07:17,940 --> 00:07:18,940
Hello, everyone.

92
00:07:19,690 --> 00:07:20,860
Nice to see you.

93
00:07:23,320 --> 00:07:24,450
Whoa.

94
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:28,620
Well, look at that.

95
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:31,410
I chose the perfect outfit
for the vibe in here.

96
00:07:32,170 --> 00:07:34,250
You said you wanted to see me?

97
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:38,170
Oh, no. I said you'd want to meet with me.

98
00:07:42,260 --> 00:07:44,640
Your email was surprising
to say the least.

99
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:50,850
Hello.

100
00:07:50,930 --> 00:07:52,980
I am Lieutenant Colonel Yang Du-gwan,

101
00:07:53,060 --> 00:07:56,060
Commander of the 103rd Division,
Military Police.

102
00:07:57,060 --> 00:07:58,900
General Gu Ja-woon…

103
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:01,990
…already knew the truth
had been covered up,

104
00:08:02,070 --> 00:08:05,620
at the time I sent Captain Lim
and Sergeant Park to the GP.

105
00:08:06,120 --> 00:08:09,620
During the investigation,
he offered rewards and pressured me,

106
00:08:09,700 --> 00:08:11,290
their direct commander.

107
00:08:11,370 --> 00:08:13,040
He threatened me with his influence

108
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:15,250
over personnel appointments.

109
00:08:20,300 --> 00:08:21,710
What did you do?

110
00:08:23,170 --> 00:08:24,050
Huh?

111
00:08:29,640 --> 00:08:30,470
What?

112
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:33,060
You better explain yourself.

113
00:08:34,310 --> 00:08:36,230
The soldier, Park Se-ung…

114
00:08:37,230 --> 00:08:38,150
Private Park Se-ung.

115
00:08:38,230 --> 00:08:41,030
Se-ung's father runs an academy
and you used your power,

116
00:08:41,110 --> 00:08:43,950
to get your son accepted, right?
You paid for it with our unit's account.

117
00:08:44,570 --> 00:08:45,400
Why could that be?

118
00:08:45,490 --> 00:08:49,580
So he could go to high school
over in… the States. Boston.

119
00:08:50,410 --> 00:08:52,910
It's a green card hack… to dodge the army.

120
00:08:55,290 --> 00:08:56,250
-Hey, hey!
-Huh?

121
00:08:56,330 --> 00:08:57,460
Don't blank out on me.

122
00:08:58,710 --> 00:09:00,550
I'm gonna need one favor.

123
00:09:06,930 --> 00:09:08,260
What an idiot.

124
00:09:16,190 --> 00:09:17,190
So then…

125
00:09:18,940 --> 00:09:20,860
what do you hope to achieve here?

126
00:09:22,070 --> 00:09:24,070
It's the word of one person.

127
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:27,450
Want one?

128
00:09:28,490 --> 00:09:29,820
You smart-ass bastard.

129
00:09:29,910 --> 00:09:31,080
Don't you dare!

130
00:09:33,450 --> 00:09:35,500
If you so much as touch a hair on my head,

131
00:09:35,580 --> 00:09:38,250
I'll blast that recording
all over social media.

132
00:09:39,830 --> 00:09:42,670
I know you're a big shot,
but there are others bigger than you.

133
00:09:50,390 --> 00:09:51,760
So what do you want?

134
00:09:51,850 --> 00:09:54,270
You have to put a stop
to the arrest warrant,

135
00:09:54,350 --> 00:09:56,560
and suspend all your operations.

136
00:09:56,640 --> 00:10:00,350
Then, I'll bring you
the original USB before the trial.

137
00:10:00,860 --> 00:10:02,230
Ah…

138
00:10:03,360 --> 00:10:05,280
Putting your neck out for your junior?

139
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:07,240
This means you work for us.

140
00:10:07,320 --> 00:10:09,820
Does Park Beom-gu agree
with this course of action?

141
00:10:10,990 --> 00:10:12,490
What about An Jun-ho?

142
00:10:13,330 --> 00:10:15,580
Jun-ho's feelings on this are immaterial.

143
00:10:16,370 --> 00:10:19,750
All I care about is keeping Jun-ho
safe from harm.

144
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:36,470
So, what's it feel like
being in cuffs?

145
00:10:36,560 --> 00:10:37,730
Just shut up.

146
00:10:41,150 --> 00:10:43,980
Jun-ho, you're going to military prison.

147
00:10:44,480 --> 00:10:47,280
It makes that little jail
on the base look like a resort.

148
00:10:53,620 --> 00:10:55,450
Hello, sir.
I'm transporting the prisoner now.

149
00:10:55,580 --> 00:10:57,790
Turn the car around.
Come back to the office.

150
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:01,670
-Repeat that, please?
-I said come back to the base.

151
00:11:01,750 --> 00:11:03,290
The arrest warrant wasn't issued.

152
00:11:03,830 --> 00:11:05,130
Is there a problem, sir?

153
00:11:05,210 --> 00:11:07,090
I thought you said
transport him to prison

154
00:11:07,170 --> 00:11:09,920
-and then go to Yongsan to find the USB--
-Staff Sergeant Park Sung-woo.

155
00:11:10,010 --> 00:11:11,430
Stop running your mouth.

156
00:11:12,390 --> 00:11:13,550
It's an order.

157
00:11:13,640 --> 00:11:15,220
Sorry, sir. Hello?

158
00:11:20,430 --> 00:11:23,060
Shit. What the fuck is that?

159
00:11:25,230 --> 00:11:27,320
This is total fucking bullshit.

160
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:37,990
How many people have you put under arrest?

161
00:11:38,080 --> 00:11:39,160
What?

162
00:11:40,500 --> 00:11:43,370
I wonder if you've cuffed anyone before?

163
00:11:44,500 --> 00:11:46,710
What the fuck are you going on about now?

164
00:11:47,710 --> 00:11:49,090
You've got a big head.

165
00:11:49,710 --> 00:11:51,050
Little Jun-ho's…

166
00:11:51,920 --> 00:11:53,180
a big boy now.

167
00:11:56,180 --> 00:11:57,640
No, it's not that.

168
00:11:59,850 --> 00:12:01,600
I've cuffed a lot of people.

169
00:12:05,730 --> 00:12:07,400
I've found these can break.

170
00:12:10,940 --> 00:12:12,490
Motherfucker.

171
00:12:27,210 --> 00:12:28,460
Oh, shit…

172
00:12:44,940 --> 00:12:48,110
Why won't this fucking open?

173
00:12:51,400 --> 00:12:53,820
Yeah, run, you asshole.

174
00:12:53,900 --> 00:12:57,570
-I'm gonna kill you next time I catch you.
-Oh, shit.

175
00:13:00,950 --> 00:13:01,910
Fuck.

176
00:13:20,760 --> 00:13:22,260
If that's the problem…

177
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:27,940
then who the hell
is gonna deal with it, huh?

178
00:13:35,150 --> 00:13:36,150
HAN HO-YEOL

179
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:38,990
I STOPPED JUN-HO'S ARREST WARRANT
FROM BEING ISSUED

180
00:13:39,070 --> 00:13:41,240
I'LL FIND THE USB DRIVE AND PROTECT HIM

181
00:13:41,330 --> 00:13:42,740
DON'T TRY TO STOP ME

182
00:14:01,470 --> 00:14:04,220
Sir, there's someone here
looking for Jun-ho.

183
00:14:05,350 --> 00:14:06,350
What?

184
00:14:06,930 --> 00:14:08,230
Jun-ho's still missing.

185
00:14:08,940 --> 00:14:12,690
Yes, she said if not him,
that maybe, um, the two of you could meet.

186
00:14:27,410 --> 00:14:28,910
You and I have met before…

187
00:14:30,920 --> 00:14:33,040
…when my little brother
was in the hospital.

188
00:14:46,680 --> 00:14:48,430
There's something I need to hear.

189
00:14:51,810 --> 00:14:54,020
Or maybe there's something
you need to tell me.

190
00:14:59,240 --> 00:15:00,910
EVIDENCE
ITEM USED TO COMMIT SUICIDE

191
00:15:00,990 --> 00:15:03,240
A while ago,
a man came to pay his respects,

192
00:15:03,320 --> 00:15:05,370
he said he was my brother's junior.

193
00:15:07,660 --> 00:15:09,870
Jun-ho.

194
00:15:15,380 --> 00:15:17,420
Jun-ho wasn't your brother's junior.

195
00:15:19,550 --> 00:15:22,470
He's the D.P. who pursued your brother.

196
00:15:26,060 --> 00:15:27,180
I'm sorry.

197
00:15:35,810 --> 00:15:37,860
There's no way
I can forgive him.

198
00:15:38,900 --> 00:15:40,360
For all that's happened.

199
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:47,700
I can't say
that I understand it either.

200
00:15:51,830 --> 00:15:54,750
But I know Jun-ho
was going to tell you the truth later.

201
00:15:56,710 --> 00:15:58,460
To take the responsibility.

202
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:08,060
You bastard. You killed him.

203
00:16:11,270 --> 00:16:13,560
After Shin Woo-suk…

204
00:16:14,810 --> 00:16:16,480
-Bastard!
-Get off him!

205
00:16:16,560 --> 00:16:20,480
Your younger brother dying that way,
Jun-ho became desperate.

206
00:16:20,570 --> 00:16:22,570
Stop!

207
00:16:23,780 --> 00:16:28,580
It was almost as if, he kept trying
to find an answer where there was none.

208
00:16:32,580 --> 00:16:34,080
It was the same for all of us,

209
00:16:35,870 --> 00:16:37,630
but for Jun-ho, especially.

210
00:16:39,290 --> 00:16:40,670
What are you saying?

211
00:16:43,630 --> 00:16:45,720
That's all just bullshit and you know it.

212
00:16:50,640 --> 00:16:52,140
Well, you're not wrong.

213
00:16:53,810 --> 00:16:54,980
Around here,

214
00:16:58,650 --> 00:17:00,520
we can't really do much.

215
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:06,320
Listen to you…

216
00:17:07,410 --> 00:17:09,160
Like nothing can be done about it.

217
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:15,410
I'm sick of it.

218
00:17:21,670 --> 00:17:25,260
Not giving up on the answer
to that question…

219
00:17:25,880 --> 00:17:27,260
…it drove me…

220
00:17:29,180 --> 00:17:31,100
and it cost my family…

221
00:17:47,820 --> 00:17:51,200
Do you believe that Private Kim Ru-ri
deserves the death penalty?

222
00:17:52,490 --> 00:17:55,080
Corporal Jeong Hyeong-beom
was shot in the thigh.

223
00:17:55,160 --> 00:17:58,170
He didn't receive medical attention
for over an hour.

224
00:18:00,710 --> 00:18:02,420
He died due to blood loss.

225
00:18:03,960 --> 00:18:06,470
The USB that An Jun-ho
wanted to give to me

226
00:18:07,260 --> 00:18:09,130
had evidence that supported that.

227
00:18:10,010 --> 00:18:13,140
You're saying it was the military
that made Corporal Jeong die?

228
00:18:14,850 --> 00:18:16,850
-That could be a stretch.
-Yes!

229
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:20,100
However, they have a duty.

230
00:18:21,940 --> 00:18:23,900
A promise to our soldiers.

231
00:18:25,230 --> 00:18:27,490
To protect them and save them

232
00:18:27,990 --> 00:18:29,910
when the soldiers got injured.

233
00:18:33,330 --> 00:18:34,330
You're right.

234
00:18:39,040 --> 00:18:40,460
Sometimes I think…

235
00:18:42,750 --> 00:18:45,630
about how the military is,
and I don't know if…

236
00:18:48,010 --> 00:18:49,970
I could send my child to serve.

237
00:19:20,750 --> 00:19:22,170
Mom.

238
00:19:23,960 --> 00:19:25,170
Jun-ho.

239
00:19:33,300 --> 00:19:34,600
Your face…

240
00:19:44,150 --> 00:19:45,400
Have you eaten yet?

241
00:19:49,740 --> 00:19:51,570
You always ask the same question.

242
00:19:53,240 --> 00:19:54,620
Thank you for the food.

243
00:20:00,540 --> 00:20:01,870
Eat the rest.

244
00:20:22,310 --> 00:20:24,390
Please don't worry, Mom.

245
00:20:25,190 --> 00:20:27,270
I have to finish something,
then I'll go back.

246
00:20:28,770 --> 00:20:29,690
Bye.

247
00:20:34,660 --> 00:20:36,160
Your base called.

248
00:20:37,280 --> 00:20:39,660
The man said to please call.

249
00:20:41,830 --> 00:20:43,750
He said he was your superior.

250
00:20:45,960 --> 00:20:47,380
The man who called me,

251
00:20:48,670 --> 00:20:50,380
he sounded desperate, son.

252
00:20:57,300 --> 00:20:59,600
How many times do I have to tell you?

253
00:20:59,680 --> 00:21:01,310
He took the original.

254
00:21:01,390 --> 00:21:03,480
Cut me some slack, all right?

255
00:21:04,560 --> 00:21:08,360
Gi-yeon's my friend.
You know, we're brothers in arms.

256
00:21:08,440 --> 00:21:11,070
Heo Gi-yeong, I'm gonna kill him.
Such a jackass.

257
00:21:11,570 --> 00:21:15,490
Sir, I only need a little information.
It would really help me.

258
00:21:15,570 --> 00:21:17,530
I really don't remember anything.
I'm telling you.

259
00:21:17,610 --> 00:21:20,240
It's time for you to go! God!

260
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:32,800
Sergeant Park, if you're gonna try
and stop me--

261
00:21:32,880 --> 00:21:33,840
No.

262
