No, I don't believe it does.

524
00:40:13,830 --> 00:40:16,420
Does a person deserve to die
because he abused someone?

525
00:40:16,500 --> 00:40:18,500
No, I don't believe they do.

526
00:40:19,760 --> 00:40:20,800
So what is your point then?

527
00:40:20,880 --> 00:40:23,090
Here's the point I'm trying to make.

528
00:40:23,880 --> 00:40:25,930
Nobody should have to die waiting,

529
00:40:26,010 --> 00:40:29,470
waiting on a captain like me to get
the order from a superior to save them.

530
00:40:34,900 --> 00:40:35,940
Cho Suk-bong.

531
00:40:38,270 --> 00:40:39,280
Kim Ru-ri.

532
00:40:41,190 --> 00:40:42,110
Jeong Hyeong-beom.

533
00:40:47,320 --> 00:40:48,620
Even Na Jung-seok.

534
00:40:53,210 --> 00:40:55,540
It's because of the systems we created.

535
00:40:56,170 --> 00:40:58,670
Those are your opinions.
We've heard enough.

536
00:41:00,250 --> 00:41:03,010
It's the individual
that is at fault in all those--

537
00:41:03,090 --> 00:41:05,970
Then why do all those individuals
happen to be lumped together?

538
00:41:08,220 --> 00:41:10,260
For what reason
did they join the military?

539
00:41:11,430 --> 00:41:14,810
To protect this country,
that's why they all joined the military.

540
00:41:17,520 --> 00:41:20,980
They all lived together,
and one of them tried to kill the others.

541
00:41:21,480 --> 00:41:23,240
The State's somehow not responsible?

542
00:41:23,320 --> 00:41:25,280
There's no proof or direct correlation?

543
00:41:26,410 --> 00:41:28,820
Can you tell me what these soldiers
signed up to defend

544
00:41:28,910 --> 00:41:30,830
and what kind of country is behind it?

545
00:41:32,790 --> 00:41:33,790
Objection!

546
00:41:34,330 --> 00:41:36,420
This entire testimony is objective…

547
00:41:36,500 --> 00:41:37,710
and unsubstantiated--

548
00:41:50,470 --> 00:41:52,390
I guess you came to find the USB?

549
00:42:00,310 --> 00:42:01,980
I'm sorry, Sergeant Han.

550
00:42:05,860 --> 00:42:07,950
I don't have the USB anymore.

551
00:42:13,450 --> 00:42:14,660
What's that mean?

552
00:42:17,210 --> 00:42:18,040
Your Honor.

553
00:42:19,120 --> 00:42:20,790
I would like to submit evidence

554
00:42:20,880 --> 00:42:23,550
that will substantiate
Captain Lim Ji-seop's testimony.

555
00:42:23,630 --> 00:42:25,130
Corporal Jeong's autopsy report

556
00:42:25,210 --> 00:42:27,880
and a second about Kim Ru-ri
that tracked his bullets.

557
00:42:29,550 --> 00:42:33,310
It is evidence that proves
that it was not an immediate death.

558
00:42:35,470 --> 00:42:37,230
Well done.

559
00:42:40,100 --> 00:42:43,020
This is the initial report
before any revisions were made.

560
00:42:43,570 --> 00:42:46,610
The source of that evidence is unknown.
That evidence is inadmissible.

561
00:42:46,690 --> 00:42:48,110
I am the source.

562
00:42:50,610 --> 00:42:53,370
Military Police, Sergeant Park Beom-gu,
Your Honor.

563
00:42:53,910 --> 00:42:55,580
You're Military Police.

564
00:42:56,120 --> 00:42:57,960
Now remember who you are!

565
00:43:01,040 --> 00:43:02,210
You're welcome, sir.

566
00:43:05,250 --> 00:43:06,170
Sergeant Park,

567
00:43:06,260 --> 00:43:07,670
it's me, An Jun-ho.

568
00:43:10,840 --> 00:43:13,050
My mother said you wanted me to call you.

569
00:43:13,760 --> 00:43:16,770
Hello, this is Shin Hye-yeon.

570
00:43:19,980 --> 00:43:21,480
I heard the whole story.

571
00:43:22,730 --> 00:43:24,440
About what happened back then.

572
00:43:26,900 --> 00:43:29,030
And what it was
that you wanted to tell me.

573
00:43:31,570 --> 00:43:32,660
I'm sorry.

574
00:43:36,120 --> 00:43:37,620
You don't need to be sorry.

575
00:43:41,670 --> 00:43:43,000
For you and I…

576
00:43:45,840 --> 00:43:47,340
what matters is tomorrow.

577
00:43:56,350 --> 00:43:58,930
I'll be the one to deliver the USB
to the court tomorrow.

578
00:43:59,020 --> 00:44:03,060
During the trial, Captain Lim will drag
things out by testifying as a witness.

579
00:44:04,690 --> 00:44:06,860
Wait, I'm confused.
